  "body": "We should show a nicely formatted map, with tls and ports. This 50% works. Today we have:\n\n```\nNAME      RULE          BACKEND   ADDRESS          AGE\nechomap   -                       130.211.10.121   5h\n          foo.bar.com   \n          /foo          echoheadersx:80\n          bar.baz.com   \n          /bar          echoheadersy:80\n          /foo          echoheadersx:80\n\n```\n\nWhich works well enough, but printing a single Ingress involves hand managing tabs and newlines till the entire Ingress is printed, i.e: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubectl/resource_printer.go#L1029\n\nSo when we start mixing different Ingress types, we get jarring output:\n\n```\nNAME                   RULE          BACKEND      ADDRESS   AGE\nanother-no-rules-map   -             haproxy:80             39s\n\n                                     echoheadersy:80\nechomap                -                       130.211.10.121   5h\n                       foo.bar.com   \n                       /foo          echoheadersx:80\n                       bar.baz.com   \n                       /bar          echoheadersy:80\n                       /foo          echoheadersx:80\n\n```\n\nThis is because the columns are formatted per the top ingress and don't match the bottom one. The tabbed writer used by kubectl to align columns gets confused on the whole. \n",
